==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[vulgaris]]'', from ''[[vulgis]]'', '''common people'''

===Adjective===
'''vulgar''' (more vulgar, most vulgar)

# ''(classical sense)'' having to do with ordinary, common people
# [[rude]], [[uncouth]], [[distasteful]]

